<HEADLINE> Germany Grants Assistance to Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The German government has agreed
to grant an assistance of 31 million German marks (17.5 million
U.S. dollars) for the implementation of four different projects in
Nepal, the Nepali RSS news agency said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The projects include family planning program, road development
program, western Nepal health program and the Middle Marsyangdi
hydro-power project in western part of the country, the RSS said.
</P>
<P>
The grant assistance is part of the total commitment made by
Germany during the annual consultations with Nepal in November
1997, the news agency said.
</P>
<P>
Germany has been aiding Nepal in the areas of rural and urban
development, hydro-power, road, health, agriculture and forestry,
it added.
</P>
<P>
Germany is a member of the Nepal Aid Group. 
</P>
</TEXT>
