<HEADLINE> URGENT  Orban Elected New Hungarian Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Viktor Orban, 35-year-old
right-wing leader, was elected Hungary's new prime minister
in a parliamentary vote Monday.
</P>
<P>
Orban, leader of the Federation of Young Democrats-Hungarian
Civic Party (Fidesz-MPP), was gained 222 votes in the parliament,
while 119 voted against him, eight abstained and 37 did not vote.
</P>
<P>
He was sworn in immediately after the parliamentary vote.
