<HEADLINE> Over 293b Rupees Collected during 1997-98 in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Chairman of the Central Board of
Revenue (CBR) of Pakistan Moeen Uddin Khan said Monday that total
revenues collected during 1997-98 (July 1-June 30) amounted to
293.058 billion rupees (about 6.37 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Addressing a press conference here at CBR, he said that
revenues collection during 1997-98 reflected an increase of 16.1
percent over the collection in the same period of the previous
fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
He said that an incentives-oriented policy was being pursued to
encourage the tax collecting officers for the realization of the
revenue targets.
</P>
<P>
However, the achieved revenue collection is still short of the
revised budget target of 298 billion rupees (about 6.47 billion
dollars).
</P>
<P>
The original revenue target set in the 1997-98 fiscal budget
stood at 324 billion rupees (about 7 billion dollars) which was
scaled down to 305 billion rupees (about 6.63 billion dollars) in
January, to 297.89 billion rupees (about 6.47 billion dollars) on
June 15.  
</P>
</TEXT>
