<HEADLINE> Germany Receives Less Industrial Orders in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Industrial orders received by Germany
in May fell 0.3 percent when compared with April, mainly due to a
decline in overseas demand, official figures released Monday by
the German Economics Ministry showed.
</P>
<P>
According to the seasonally adjusted data, Germany's total
domestic orders in May remained unchanged from the level of the
previous month while foreign orders were down 0.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
However, when measured against the same month of last year,
Germany's total industrial orders rose 6.1 percent. 
</P>
