<HEADLINE> Bridge Collapse Kills 11 in S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Eleven workers were killed
and 14 others were injured Monday when a bridge under
construction collapsed at Bushbuckridge in Mpumalanga Province,
northeast of South Africa.
</P>
<P>
Rescuers feared the number of people killed in the accident
could rise as the search for survivors and bodies continued on
Monday evening, South African Press Association (SAPA) reported.
</P>
<P>
Jan de Beer, coordinator at the Life Crisis Control Center in
Nelspruit, about 300 km northeast of Johannesburg, was quoted as
saying that five of the 14 injured were in a serious condition.
They would be airlifted to a private hospital in Nelspruit.
</P>
<P>
De Beer said the bridge, which was being built across a river,
apparently collapsed when one of the pillars gave way.
</P>
<P>
Peter Price, spokesman for Concorde Construction, the company
responsible for the construction of the bridge, said it was not
immediately clear what caused the pillar to collapse.
</P>
<P>
"We are not sure what happened. We were still constructing
the bridge when it collapsed," Price said. 
</P>
