<DOCNO> XIE19980707.0039 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania's Budget to Be Altered for Insufficient Income </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The 1998 budget of Romania will
have to be altered, only two months after being endorsed by the
parliament, the local daily Nine O'clock Monday cited Finance
Minister Daniel Daianu as saying.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that this measure was needed to keep the
budget deficit "within the safety zone" as the budget income in
the first semester of this year was less than expected. "A budget
deficit over 5.5 percent is a very bad thing for the national
economy," he added.
</P>
<P>
The Finance Ministry has to alter the income accomplishment
program because of the 9.4 percent GDP drop in the first part of
1998. The program for the first semester stipulated 33.986
trillion lei (about 3.54 billion U.S. dollar) budget income, but
only 32.673 trillion lei (3.4 billion dollars) was collected in
the end, a figure which represents 40 percent of the state budget
income.
</P>
<P>
Direct taxes (on profit and salaries) and custom taxes were
collected in full, and even exceeded expectations, but indirect
taxes (VAT, excise taxes) did not come through, according to data
given by the Finance Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The budget income is to be altered to 32.567 trillion lei (3.39
billion dollars) for the first semester of the year, sources of
the ministry informed.
</P>
<P>
The budget adaptations will be operated top down, Finance
Minister Daianu announced, but he did not yet name the ministries
which would have to cut expenses.
</P>
<P>
The targets in the 1998 budget adopted on May read a 3.6
percent-of-the-GDP budget deficit, and zero economic growth.
Budget revenues are set at 75.044 trillion lei (7.82 billion
dollars), and the spendings at 97.902 trillion (10.2 billion
dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
