<HEADLINE> Death Toll Rises to 13 in S. African Bridge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The death toll in a bridge
collapse in South Africa's Mpumalanga Province rose to 13 on
Monday night with the discovery of another body in the rubble and
the death of a victim in hospital.
</P>
<P>
Rescue workers, with the help of sniff dogs, were still trying
to find signs of life in the debris Monday evening, South African
national television reported.
</P>
<P>
Eleven people were confirmed dead after the Bushbuckridge
bridge, which was still under construction, collapsed at about 1
p.m. (1100 GMT) when a pillar apparently gave way.
</P>
<P>
Five of the 14 people injured were airlifted to hospital in a
serious condition.
</P>
<P>
Police have launched investigation into the cause of the
accident. 
</P>
