presidential affair and cover-up. Starr's spokesman, Charles
Bakaly, said over the weekend that the grand jury has been asking
a lot of questions and that Starr is moving the probe along as
quickly as possible.
</P>
<P>
Tripp testified last Tuesday and Thursday before the grand
jury. The probe was triggered by Tripp's 20 hours of secretly
recorded phone calls with Lewinsky in which the former intern
confided an alleged affair with President Bill Clinton. 
