<HEADLINE> Southwestern Chinese Railway Line Resumes Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The railway line from Chengdu,
capital of southwest China's Sichuan Province to Kunming, capital
of Yunnan Province, resumed operation yesterday morning after
having been closed for a day because of a mud slide triggered by
torrential rains.
</P>
<P>
The section of the railway line from Yonglang to Puba was
covered by mud and rocks that caused a passenger train to derail,
and two cars to be covered with mud. No casualties have been
reported so far.
</P>
<P>
More than 200 railway workers and 400 armed police rushed to
the scene to help with rescue operations.  
</P>
