<HEADLINE> Southwestern Chinese City Preparing For Major Flood </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The southwestern Chinese city of
Chongqing is preparing to battle the largest flood this year on
the Yangtze River, which is expected to hit the city tomorrow
evening.
</P>
<P>
Pu Haiqing, Chongqing's mayor, inspected flood-prevention and
control work, there today.
</P>
<P>
According to a local flood-control official, the highest flood
level -- 212 meters -- on the river this year, a meter above the
danger line, will hit Zhutuo, a part of Chongqing, tomorrow at
noon. And a peak of 180 meters, more than a meter above the danger
level, will hit the urban area of Chongqing at 11:00 p.m tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, about 1,600 people are now
monitoring the flood situation carefully, and 66,000 people have
been organized to fight it.  
</P>
