<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe to Review Civil Service Reforms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Heads of the Zimbabwean government
ministries will hold a workshop Thursday and Friday to discuss
aspects of the second phase of the public service reform program.
</P>
<P>
This was announced by the office of the president and cabinet
and the public service commission in a joint statement Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The framework of the second phase covers the period between
1998 and 2000.
</P>
<P>
The first phase (1991-95) focused on improving efficiency in
the government and how services would be provided by a reduced
civil service.
</P>
<P>
The second phase would be part of the Zimbabwe program for
economic and social transformation and vision 2020 programs on
medium and long term planning.
</P>
<P>
The reforms would see the creation of a small, but efficient
public service.
</P>
<P>
At present, there are over 170,000 public service people in
Zimbabwe, causing big expenditure in the government budget and
bringing heavy burden on to the government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
