<HEADLINE> Russian Stock Prices Plunge Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices on the Russian Trading
System (RTS) continued to slide Tuesday, with blue chips tumbling
seven to 10 percent in the first two hours in an apparent sign of
the country's deepening financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
The RTS index plunged 9.17 percent to 131.71 with a volume of
only 9.78 million U.S. dollars by 13:00 local time (07:00 GMT),
the Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The slump was attributed to dwindling confidence in the Russian
economy's ability to stabilize as many traders try to dispose of
their portfolios in favor of a safe haven in foreign currency.
</P>
<P>
The failure of the auction of the oil company Rosneft, rising
yields on treasury bills, the delay of an IMF decision on a
stabilization loan and persistent rumors of a ruble devaluation
also fueled the downturn. 
