<HEADLINE> Guivarc'h Vow to Break Scoring Drought </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 7 (Xinhua) -- French striker Guivarc'h has vowed to
break his scoring drought when his team play Croatia in the World Cup
semifinals on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"Like all striker I am obsessed with goals. That will pay off one
day," he said Monday in Clairefontaine southwest of Paris.
</P>
<P>
"It's true that I have yet to score a goal, but the team's
performance and winning are what's most important, not individual
goals," he said.
</P>
<P>
The 27-year-old forward expected Croatia would use the same tactics
as the Italians in the quarterfinals.
</P>
<P>
"Playing against Croatia will be very exciting. I can't wait to
play. I'm very confident that we can win because we're ready to play."
</P>
<P>
Guivarc'h, bound for the club side Newcastle after the World Cup,
said he yearned to be part of the English soccer.
</P>
<P>
"I love the atmosphere in English stadiums and I can't wait to be a
part of it," he said.
