<HEADLINE> CPPCC Chairman Meets With Romanian Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Li Ruihuan, a member of the
Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC), met here today
with Romania's Democratic Party delegation led by vice-president
Alexandru Sassu.
</P>
<P>
Li, concurrently chairman of the National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference, first extended
his welcome to Sassu on behalf of the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
The Sino-Romania relationship has withstood tests despite
changes in the international and domestic situations in both
countries, Li said.
</P>
<P>
Chinese people are also delighted with the achievements of
Romania, he said.
</P>
<P>
Regarding party-to-party relationships, Li said the Democratic
Party of Romania (DPR), as an important ruling party, plays an
indispensable role in the political life of Romania.
</P>
<P>
The CPC, like the DPR, shoulders the enormous task of
developing the economy and improving people's lives in its
country, Li said, expressing his hope to strengthen exchanges and
cooperation between the two parties on the basis of the four
principles guiding party-to-party relationships (independence,
entire equality, mutual respect and non-interference in each
other's internal affairs), and to bring a long-term, stable,
healthy and comprehensive Sino-Romanian relationship into the 21st
century.
</P>
<P>
Sassu sent DPR President Peter Roman's warm regards to Li,
adding that Roman had accepted Li's invitation to visit China and
hopes to make the trip as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
Sassu told Li that he was deeply impressed by the great
progress China has made. The DPR wishes to further develop its
relationship with the CPC and exchange experiences with each other
on developing an economy, he said. 
</P>
