<HEADLINE> Fund Endorsed to Support Mother-Tongue Teaching in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The Standing Committee on
Language Education and Research (SCOLAR) of Hong Kong on Tuesday
endorsed the award of 11.6 million HK dollars (1.49 million U.S.
dollars) to the University of Hong Kong to set up a support center
for teachers using Chinese as the medium of instruction.
</P>
<P>
The support center is one of SCOLAR's major recommendations to
the government of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(HKSAR) under a package of measures in support of the
mother-tongue teaching policy which is due to take effect at the
beginning of the 1998-99 school year.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the support center, the package includes the
provision of a one-off grant for Chinese-medium schools to
organize school-based English Enhancement Programs and to set up
an English Corner within each school on a voluntary basis.
</P>
<P>
The package was accepted by the SAR government earlier this
year as it will provide additional support for Chinese-medium
school students in English language learning and for teachers
switching from English medium of instruction to Chinese.
</P>
<P>
The whole package will cost about 68 million HK dollars (8.72
million U.S. dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
