<HEADLINE> Opening China's Construction Projects To Public Bidding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Wei Jianxing, a member of the
Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Communist Party
of China Central Committee, recently said China's public
construction project contracts must open to bidding across the
country.
</P>
<P>
Wei made the remarks at a national construction meeting July 6
and 7 in east China's Jiangsu Province, where he said that all
construction projects, except those involving national security
and disaster relief will need to be opened to public bidding as a
matter of openness, fairness, and equal competition. The move is
meant to prevent corruption and to ensure efficiency and quality.
</P>
<P>
He said that, by the end of year, all cities above the
prefecture level should have construction markets, a kind of
trading center for construction projects, and all projects should
go through legal formalities. Any interference in the process by
individuals, work units or any other irregularities will be
severely penalized. 
</P>
</TEXT>
