<HEADLINE> Indonesia, Malaysia Signs Agreement on Forest Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia and Malaysia have signed
a memorandum of understanding (MOU) on cooperation on coping with
natural disasters, particularly in prevention of forest fires and
the haze.
</P>
<P>
This was stated by visiting Malaysian Information Minister Dato
Mohamad Rahmat who met Indonesian President B.J. Habibie at the
Presidential Palace here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The cooperation will cover the exchange of information, the
prevention of forest fires and an action plan on overcoming forest
fires and the haze, Rahmat said.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, he said, President Habibie gave guidance on
how to cope with forest fires.
</P>
<P>
Rahmat told reporters that Malaysia suffered severe losses due
to Indonesia's forest fires.
</P>
<P>
However, he declined to give details on the losses the country
has sustained in such sectors as tourism, industry and development
projects.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that Malaysia last year earmarked tens of
million Malaysian ringgit to put out forest fires in Indonesia and
overcome the haze that reached Malaysia. 
</P>
