<HEADLINE> 34 Die of Gastroenteritis in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 7 (Xinhua) -- An outbreak of gastroenteritis
has claimed at least 34 lives in the past week in three districts
of far-western Nepal, press reports said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Eighteen and 10 died respectively in Bajura and Achham
districts, while in Baitadi district, at least six people have
succumbed to the disease, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
More than 400 people have died of gastroenteritis, typhoid and
fever across the Himalayan kingdom during the summer season,
official figures show.
</P>
<P>
Unhygienic conditions including unsafe drinking water during
the monsoon season which lasts from June to September are blamed
for hundreds of deaths of diseases every year in the country.
</P>
<P>
Inadequate health facilities including lack of medicine and
doctors particularly in the remote and hilly areas have
contributed to the death toll. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
