<DOCNO> XIE19980707.0104 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Sets Up Institute on Sustainable Oasis Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Academy of Sciences
(CAS) today established a research institute in northwest China's
Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region to seek solutions to
desertification and sustainable development of oases.
</P>
<P>
With over 300 research fellows and experts, the CAS Xinjiang
Ecological and Geographic Research Institute will focus on studies
of ecological preservation and agricultural development at oases
sites. The institute now operates five laboratories and three
field experiment stations to study land desertification, soil
salinization, and the deterioration of pasture land in Xinjiang's
vast and dry land expanse.
</P>
<P>
Chen Yiyu, vice-president of the CAS, said the study of oasis
ecology and the improvement of oases environments is a frontier
subject vital to the sustainable development of the economy of
Northwest China, including Xinjiang.
</P>
<P>
Although oases constitute only 4.25 percent of Xinjiang's total
area of 1.65 million square kilometers, they are major production
and residential centers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
