<HEADLINE> Saint-Denis Organizes International Youths Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAIN-DENIS, France, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The city of Saint-Denis
where the Stade de France is located is having another World Cup
-- that of youths from around the world in a week-long gala for
friendship, music, dance and football.
</P>
<P>
Some 700 teenagers of 37 national delegations have been here
since July 5 celebrating the World Cup season which is a symbol of
multiculturalism and worldwide solidarity, according to the
organizers.
</P>
<P>
The festival, initiated by Printemps network specialized in
discovering youths of talents and backed by the local city
government, is open for all.
</P>
<P>
Mustapha Terki, manager of Printemps and one of the organizers,
said that the festival is not for the confrontation of national
flags, but for a rally of communities around one festival.
</P>
<P>
Apart from singing and dancing, the participants also held
football matches.
</P>
<P>
Among the participants are a group of Algerian youths who
memorized the assassinated Berber singer Matoub Lounes, and seven
Bosnian teenagers from the once war-torn city of Tuzla. 
</P>
