<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Boeing Forecasts Rapid Growth in China's Air Transport Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 7 (Xinhua) -- China's air transport industry
should grow at an average annual rate of 9.5 percent in the next
20 years, according to Boeing's Current Market Outlook.
</P>
<P>
The forecast represents the highest growth rate for the world
air transport industry and nearly doubles the global mean figure,
according to the yearly magazine.
</P>
<P>
The outlook, known as an important strategic forecast by
aviation industry decision-makers around the world, also envisions
that China will add 1,800 jetliners worth 125 billion U.S. dollars
to its passenger fleet during the same period.
</P>
<P>
The estimate is based on China's buoyant economic growth, which
has been at a rate 2.5 times faster than that in North America and
Europe during the past two decades, Boeing says China will have
one of the most rapidly growing economies in the world for the
next 20 years.
</P>
<P>
China's airlines handled 56.3 million passengers and 1.24
million tons of cargo last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
