<HEADLINE> Sudan, Malaysia to Strengthen Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The Foreign Ministers of Sudan
and Malaysia Tuesday discussed two-way trade payment and air
cooperation between Malaysia Airlines (MAS) and Sudan's national
carrier.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia is contemplating to buy at reasonable prices cooking
oil, beef and mutton from Sudan which is a supplier of meat to
the Gulf states, Malaysian Foreign Minister Abdullah Ahmad Badawi
said after meeting his Sudanese counterpart Mustafa Osman Ismail
here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Sudan in return has expressed interest in buying on credit palm
oil from Malaysia, he said.
</P>
<P>
