Department Abdul Hamid Othman who also met the Sudanese foreign
minister, Sudan has also agreed to provide suitable land to
Malaysia's PadiBeras Nasional Sdn Bhd (Bernas) (National Rice
Company) for paddy cultivation and Tabung Haji for oil palm
plantation.
</P>
<P>
Abdul Hamid told reporters after the meeting that Mustafa
expressed his government's thanks to Malaysia for being the
driving force behind Sudan's opening up to the outside world.
</P>
<P>
Sudan is also thankful to Malaysia for the help in the
country's development, especially the cooperation extended by
Petronas (Malaysia's national oil company) in the field of oil
production, he said.
</P>
<P>
The pipe-laying project covering 1,500 kilometers through the
desert to Port Sudan would help to spur growth in settlement areas
along the route, Abdul Hamid said.
</P>
<P>
Mustafa also called on Mahathir and Malaysian Deputy Prime
Minister Anwar Ibrahim.
</P>
<P>
The Sudanese foreign minister, accompanied by Governor of the
Bank of Sudan Sabir Mohammed Elhassan and other senior officials,
arrived here Monday for a five-day visit to Malaysia. 
