<HEADLINE> Croatian Goal-keeper to Answer Criticism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Croatian goal-keeper Drazen Ladic has
conceded only one goal in the World Cup finals but were still rated
the worst among the four goal-keepers left in the tournament.
</P>
<P>
Former Scotland goal-keeper Bob Wilson said Ladic is the worst
of the four goal-keepers after Dutch Edwin van der Sar, Brazilian
Claudio Taffarel and Frenchman Fabien Barthez.
</P>
<P>
"Ladic is perhaps the most flawed of the remaining four keepers.
Goal-keeping is about consistency and it is the crucial feature
which he lacks." said Wilson.
</P>
<P>
But the 35-year-old Croatian veteran has a chance to hit back at
the criticism when his team play against hosts France in Wednesday's
semi-final match at Saint-Denis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
