<HEADLINE> Brian Laudrup to Quit International Football </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Brian Laudrup has announced that he
would like to quit international football to put all his efforts
into making a success of his move to Chelsea.
</P>
<P>
Brian Laudrup, 29, said he would follow his elder brother
Michael into international retirement:"I've got a footballing
hangover. It's time for a younger player to take my place."
</P>
<P>
"I'm stopping after one of the biggest matches the Danish team
have ever played," said Brian Laudrup, "I have had enough after
reaching a World Cup quarter-final and winning the European title."
</P>
<P>
Brian has informed Denmark coach Bo Johansson of his decision
after the Denmark-Brazil match. He made his Denmark debut in 1987
and has scored 21 goals for Denmark in 82 matches. 
