<HEADLINE> Mozambique-S. African Agro Program Hailed as </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The agricultural development
program jointly undertaken by Mozambique and South Africa was
hailed as a success, with some unnegligible problems.
</P>
<P>
This conclusion was drawn from a preliminary study by the
Research Center of the Mozambican Rural Mutual Aid Association #,
Noticias daily reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Joao Uthui, an official involved in the study said that the
major problem with the program is that there is no clear
definition to the real aim to the program, which is affecting the
coordination between the investors and local governments.
</P>
<P>
Uthui said that the difference in the forms of investment and
income distribution results in unfair participation in the
development of natural resources.
</P>
<P>
About 1,500 local Mozambicans were involved in the development
program jointly undertaken by 25 South African Boer farmers and
25 Mozambican partners.
</P>
<P>
The program was initiated by Mozambican President Joaquim
Chissano and his South African counterpart Nelson Mandela in May
1996, with 2,000 hectares.  
</P>
