<HEADLINE> BOC Centralizes International Telegraphic Exchanges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of China (BOC) recently
became the first Chinese bank to centralize international
telegraphic exchanges in a bid to reduce financial risks.
</P>
<P>
The new system, introduced on June 1, places all transmission,
receiving, transfer, inquiry and management operations under the
control of the BOC's headquarters in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
According to a bank official, the new management system is
designed to help prevent and reduce financial risks, as well as
improve the bank's efficiency.
</P>
<P>
The BOC, a bank with an excellent international reputation,
has also established a complete telegraphic communications network
with major banks around the world.  
