<HEADLINE> Philippine President Vows to Be Pro-Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Joseph Estrada
Tuesday assured the business community that his administration
would create an economic environment conducive to free
competition.
</P>
<P>
In a dialogue with foreign and local business leaders in the
Presidential Palace, Estrada said that under his regime, investors
would enjoy the least amount of regulations and the greatest
number of opportunities.
</P>
<P>
To just start this effort, he mobilized the Economic Monitoring
and Mobilization Task Force to respond to the policy concerns of
the business sector and called for the greater cooperation between
the government and the business sector.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Estrada said the new government would commit itself
to pursuing all the political and economic reforms installed by
the previous administration that will improve the lives of most
people by way of either lower commodity prices or more jobs.
</P>
<P>
While reiterating his commitment to instituting
economic-friendly policies, Estrada said the other priorities of
his administration are to restore peace and order, eradicate
poverty, abolish the pork barrel funds for the congress and stamp
out corruption.
</P>
<P>
The business leaders assured Estrada of their support for the
new government.
</P>
