<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT, July 7 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- The Indian government claimed Monday that there
was no change in its basic position on what it calls the
discriminatory nature of the Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty (CTBT).
</P>
<P>
Indian press has indicated lately that the government's
position on the CTBT is shifting from criticism toward
consideration of joining if certain concessions in technology
transfer are secured. (India-Test Ban Treaty)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- France has decided to recognize a Palestinian
state if it is declared after the interim agreement between the
Palestinians and Israel ends next May, a report on the Israeli
Ha'aretz newspaper said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted sources in Paris as saying that the decision
was made with a consensus among France's top leaders, including
President Jacques Chirac, Prime Minister Lionel Jospin and Foreign
Minister Hubert Vedrine. (Israel-France-Palestinian State)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TIRANA -- More than 500 Albanian soldiers joined a war game on
Sunday in the country's northern Skurraj and Burbini regions near
Kosovo, a province of Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Code-named "Skurraj 98," the war game was the fourth and
largest so far this year in Albania, and the only one involving
air and ground forces in combined military operations.
(Albania-War Game)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BANGKOK -- Thai Foreign Minister Surin Pitsuwan begins an
eight-day visit to Singapore, Indonesia and Australia on Tuesday,
The Nation newspaper reported.
</P>
<P>
In Singapore, Surin will hold talks with his counterpart there
to seek cooperation in boosting bilateral trade. He will also
raise the need for ASEAN (Association of Southeast Asian Nations)
to adopt a "constructive intervention" policy. (Thailand-FM Visit)
</P>
