<HEADLINE> Postal Service Issues Buddhist Mountain Postcards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The State Postal Service Bureau
recently issued a set of postcards featuring ten major temples
on Wutai Mountain, one of China's major Buddhist mountains.
</P>
<P>
Wutai Mountain, located in north China's Shanxi Province, is
one the nation's four Buddhist mountain shrines. Some 47 temple
complexes have been built on the mountain since the Tang Dynasty
(608-907), and Wutai is widely recognized as "a museum of ancient
Chinese architecture",
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Posts and Telecommunications also issued
special stamps in 1997 showing ancient temples on Wutai
Mountain. 
</P>
