<HEADLINE> Albania Stages War Game in North </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, July 6 (Xinhua) -- More than 500 Albanian soldiers
joined a war game on Sunday in the countery's northern Skurraj and
Burbini regions near Kosovo, of Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Codenamed "Skurraj 98," the war game was the fourth and largest
so far this year in Albania, and the only one involving air and
ground forces in combined military operations.
</P>
<P>
The aviation, infantry, artillery, anti-chemical warfare and
special forces were backed by two fighter-bombers, two
helicopters, and dozens of tanks and armored vehicles.
</P>
<P>
The one-day exercise was aimed at enhancing officers' ability
to carry out military planning, organizing and commanding jobs,
and at promoting the military's capability of combined operations.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Fatos Nano, Defense Minister Luan Hajdaraga and
Chief of General Staff Aleks Andoni were there to see the exercise.
</P>
<P>
After the game, Hajdaraga told participating soldiers that such
exercise was of special significance at a time when armed clashes
in Kosovo could further escalate in spite of recent peace talks.
</P>
<P>
Ethnic Albanians, who account for 90 percent of the population
in Kosovo, a southern province in the Serb republic of the
Yugoslav Federation, were fighting for independence from Belgrade.
</P>
<P>
Given the circumstance, said Hajdaraga, military exercises
could help build up confidence, security and stability. 
</P>
