<HEADLINE> Thai FM to Begin Foreign Tour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Thai Foreign Minister Surin
Pitsuwan begins an eight-day visit to Singapore, Indonesia and
Australia on Tuesday, The Nation newspaper reported.
</P>
<P>
In Singapore, Surin will hold talks with his counterpart to
seek cooperation in boosting bilateral trade. He will also raise
the need for ASEAN (Association of Southeast Asian Nations) to
adopt a "constructive intervention" policy.
</P>
<P>
Thailand will seek Singapore's opinions on the policy, also
known as "flexible engagement," Thai Foreign Ministry spokesman
Kobsak Chutikul was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
