<HEADLINE> German Arrested over French Gendarme Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 6 (Xinhua) -- A German Soccer hooligan was arrested
Monday in Hamburg and charged with the attempted murder of a
French gendarme who is still in a coma after being attacked by
thugs during the World Cup in France, according to reports from
Hanover.
</P>
<P>
Hanover prosecutors said the 24-year-old, named as Tobias R.,
was "strongly suspected" of involvement in the attack on Daniel
Nivel on June 21.
</P>
<P>
The 43-year-old Nivel was clubbed to the ground and kicked
after a group of around 50 fans ran riot at the end of
Germany-Yugoslavia match in the eastern French town of Lens.
</P>
<P>
Tobias R. was arrested at his home early Monday on charges of
attempted murder and causing serious bodily harm, and of
threatening public order.
</P>
<P>
When questioned, he admitted being in the vicinity of the
attack, but denied being directly involved in the assault on
Nivel. However prosecutors said they had used eyewitness reports
and photographs to identify him.
</P>
<P>
He had been questioned by German police over the incident once
before, but was released due to a lack of evidence.
</P>
<P>
Tobias R. is the first German hooligan to be charged in Germany
in connection with the attack. Other suspects arrested on the
basis of photographic material were released for lack of evidence.
</P>
<P>
Two other Germans have already been arrested in France over the
attack.
</P>
<P>
The French police union SGP said it had evidence that neo-Nazis
had orchestrated the violence in Lens. 
</P>
</TEXT>
