<HEADLINE> Construction of Hainan Airport Proceeds Smoothly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Construction of the Meilan
International Airport in Haikou of China's southernmost island
province Hainan, is proceeding smoothly and the facility will be
completed by the end of this year at a total cost of 2.3 billion
yuan.
</P>
<P>
Projects initiated in December last year and scheduled for
completion this July include the control tower with an operational
area of 5,152 sq.m., the parking apron covering 128,000 sq.m., the
terminal building with a floor space of 60,000 sq.m., and a runway
some 3,600 meters long and 45 meters wide.
</P>
<P>
The world-class airport will feature state-of-the-art fuel
supply and power generation systems, as well as imported
control tower, communications and computer equipment.
</P>
<P>
Meilan Airport will relieve pressure on the Haikou Airport
which lacks a sufficient passenger handling capacity. 
</P>
