<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Spanish 500cc rider Carlos Checa,
who crashed during practice for the British Grand Prix, was
described as "comfortable" in intensive care after suffering a
stroke, reports reaching here said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Graham Lennox, the consultant neurosurgeon at Queen's Medical
Center in Nottingham, said that Checa, who ranked fourth in the
world championship standings, had his spleen removed as an
emergency procedure when he was admitted to the hospital following
his crash on Friday.
</P>
<P>
"He was making an excellent recovery, but unfortunately
suffered a stroke on Sunday and was immediately taken to the
hospital's intensive care unit," Lennox said.
</P>
<P>
