<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bulgaria, Turkey Sign Free Trade Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The Bulgarian and Turkish governments
signed an agreement on Monday which lowers tariffs of industrial
products by 70 percent and aims at fully liberalizing the trade of
industrial products between the two countries by 2002.
</P>
<P>
The agreement will take effect on January 1, 1999, Bulgarian
Trade Minister Valentin Vassilev told the press.
</P>
<P>
The tariff on agricultural products will be reduced at a slower
pace, on the basis of quota systems.
</P>
<P>
Considering the large trade surplus Bulgaria enjoyed in the
bilateral trade, it would benefit more from the agreement, said
Vassilev.
</P>
<P>
It was the most favorable trade agreement by far yet signed by
Bulgaria, he said.
</P>
<P>
Bulgarian exports to Turkey amount to 440 million U.S. dollars
annually, 80 percent of the total mutual trade volume between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
Oil products, fertilizers, sugar, and minerals are among
Bulgaria's main exports. 
</P>
</TEXT>
