<HEADLINE> IAAF Supports Moscow as Grand Prix Final Venue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The International Amateur Athletic
Federation said Monday the IAAF would still stage the Golden
League-Grand Prix final in Moscow on September 5 despite calls for
the venue to be changed, according to reports from Monaco.
</P>
<P>
IAAF press chief Giorgio Reineri said on Monday: "We have no
plans to change the venue of the final.
</P>
<P>
"We have financial guarantees from the Russian federation and
the City of Moscow and continue to be confident that the meeting
will be successfully staged there."
</P>
<P>
Reineri added that the IAAF itself would be paying for the
athletes' travel, accommodation and prize money. 
</P>
