<BODY>
<HEADLINE> East China's Zhejiang Province Improving Investment Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Zhejiang Province on the east
China coast has been redoubling efforts since the beginning of
this year to improve the environment for overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
The province has institute some twenty new measures aimed at
improving the "software" environment for overseas investors, and
has invested heavily in upgrading its infrastructure, or
"hardware" environment.
</P>
<P>
According to these measures, the better developed prefectures
and prefectural-level cities, and counties and county-level
cities, are all expected to set up specialized organizations to
provide overseas investors with free services.
</P>
<P>
While urging prefectures, cities and counties to simplify
procedures for getting overseas-financed projects approved, they
are not allowed to install new programs for collecting fees from
overseas investors. And fee-collecting programs already in place
are expected to be abolished.
</P>
<P>
The province has also published ten articles of preferential
policies to encourage direct foreign investment in productive
projects, infrastructure, high-tech industries, and economic
development zones above the provincial level.
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang has also intensified overseas investment promotion
activities by sending trade missions to European countries to
publicize the province, and has participated in a trade fair held
in Hong Kong in early June. The province plans to complete
compilation of an investment project database sometime this year.
</P>
<P>
From January to May, Zhejiang Province approved 379
overseas-financed projects involving the contractual use of 638
million U.S. dollars of overseas investment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
