<HEADLINE> Kasparov to Launch Internet Site </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, July 6 (Xinhua) -- World chess champion Garry Kasparov
of Russia said Monday he will launch an internet site for chess
lovers eager to watch real-time matches and a chance to take on
grandmasters.
</P>
<P>
Speaking in a press conference here, Kasparov said the Club
Kasparov site will go live by October with chess news, coverage of
events, answers to questions by chess champions and instructions
for newcomers to the game.
</P>
<P>
He noted that "Chess belongs to computers, it belongs to the
internet. There is no other game that can be played real-time on
the internet."
</P>
<P>
"The club will be open to all and aim to satisfy the curiosity
of all people in chess," Kasparov added. 
</P>
