<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian Golden-haired Orangutans Moved To Southwestern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, July 7 (Xinhua) -- A pair of rare young
golden-haired orangutans from Indonesia have been moved to a zoo
in the city of Chongqing in southwestern Chinas family, as a gift
of the Indonesian government.
</P>
<P>
The orangutan, Pongo pygmaeus, usually reaches sexual maturity
at the age of 7 and may live for 50 years. The pair, a male named
Boby and female named Laila, were given the most luxurious house
at the Chongqing Zoo.
</P>
<P>
Their keeper says that they are happy with visitors and do not
mind when their hands are touched, but they do seem to have some
problem communicating with the keeper.
</P>
<P>
"They are not familiar with the Chinese language and respond
only to 'yes' and 'no'," the keeper explains.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
