<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.N. Chief Says Kosovo Conflict Impact May Spill over </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, July 6 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi
Annan has warned that the deteriorating situation in Kosovo could
potentially destabilize the entire Balkan region.
</P>
<P>
In a new report to the U.N. Security Council, which was
disclosed by the U.N. Department of Public Information on Monday,
Annan said a new outbreak of violence in Kosovo caused some 6,900
refugees to flee to Albania by the end of June.
</P>
<P>
In addition, over 10,000 people have been internally displaced
within the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia, while approximately
45,000 have been displaced within Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
He called on the parties concerned to demonstrate restraint and
resume negotiations to find a peaceful solution to the conflict.
</P>
<P>
"I am increasingly concerned that unless hostilities in Kosovo
are stopped, tensions could spill across borders and destabilize
the entire region," he said.
</P>
<P>
Kosovo is a province of Serbia. Most of its population are
ethnic Albanians. Over 200 people have reportedly been killed this
year in clashes between Serbian forces and the underground Kosovo
Liberation Army which is seeking independence from Serbia.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
