<HEADLINE> German Soccer Fan Detained for Attacking French </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 6 (Xinhua) -- German police said Monday that they
had detained another German soccer fan suspected of taking part in
an attack on a French policeman on the fringes of a World Cup
match in France last month.
</P>
<P>
The 24-year-old man was held Monday in the northern German city
of Hamburg on a warrant accusing him of attempted murder.
</P>
<P>
The 43-year-old French gendarme suffered serious head injures
and has been in a coma since the attack by several German football
hooligans after the World Cup game between Germany and Yugoslavia
on June 21 in the northern French city of Lens.
</P>
<P>
Two other Germans were already arrested last month in France in
connection with the assault.  
</P>
</TEXT>
