<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Britain, Peru to Further Trade Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Britain's Labor government will
promote its trade cooperation with Peru in an effort to increase
its market share in Latin America, according to British government
officials.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a briefing Monday before Peruvian President Alberto
Fujimori's visit to Britain, British officials said although
British exports to Peru have increased over the past few years,
Britain's market share in Peru remains weak.
</P>
<P>
"The UK has a poor market share in Latin America. The talks
with Peru are part of efforts to address this," said one British
official.
</P>
<P>
The Officials also noted that the British government is pleased
with the measures taken by Peruvian government to end Peru's
cocaine production but is expected to urge for more action.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that Britain has just provided 250 million
pounds (about 410 million U.S. dollars) in aid to Peru to help the
country fight against drugs trade.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
